properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 9:33PM CST until January 15 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Icy Wednesday Morning Commute...

.A quick moving system will bring freezing drizzle and very light
freezing rain to the area. The precipitation will spread into the
area from the south and the west overnight through daybreak, and
last through the morning commute. Untreated roads and sidewalks,
along with bridges and overpasses will be especially vulnerable to
icing. Plan now for potential travel impacts during the morning
commute.

* WHAT...Freezing drizzle and very light freezing rain expected.
Total ice accumulations of a light glaze to less than a tenth of
an inch.

* WHERE...Portions of east central, northeast and southeast Iowa
and north central and northwest Illinois.

* WHEN...From 2 AM to noon CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Very slippery sidewalks, roads and bridges are
possible. The hazardous conditions could impact the morning
commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Eventually temperatures will rise above
freezing from south to north by mid morning on Wednesday ending
the threat for freezing drizzle. Until this occurs, slick roads
and other surfaces will be possible.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling. Prepare for possible
power outages.

In Illinois, go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road
conditions. In Iowa, call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO NOON CST WEDNESDAY
